# QA evidence links in GitHub issues

When filing or commenting on QA findings (`qa` label) or run reports (`qa-run`):

- **Run folder links** (Evidence, "Found in run", dedup comments): use the GitHub **tree** URL:
  `https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/tree/qa-evidence/<run-id>`
- **Inline screenshots** in issue bodies: use **raw** file URLs:
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<owner>/<repo>/qa-evidence/<run-id>/screenshots/...`

Never link to a raw directory URL (`raw.githubusercontent.com/.../<run-id>/`) — it always 404s because GitHub raw does not serve directory listings.

`pnpm qa:publish-evidence` prints the tree URL on line 1 and `raw-screenshots-base=…` on line 2.
